# CODEOWNERS — auto-route reviews to the right team for security-sensitive paths.
# Placeholder team names; replace `@nexus-eng/...` with the actual GitHub org teams.

# Hypervisor + sandbox: the security-critical core. Phase A typed the
# failure surface; Phase C adds the daemon; both want extra eyes.
src/hypervisor/**            @nexus-eng/security @nexus-eng/runtime
src/sandbox/**               @nexus-eng/security @nexus-eng/runtime

# LLM recovery path: the only egress to external services, with attacker-
# influenced inputs. Threat-model owner reviews every change.
src/hypervisor/llm_policy.rs @nexus-eng/llm @nexus-eng/security
docs/security_threat_model_phase_b.md @nexus-eng/llm @nexus-eng/security

# Daemon binary + protocol: cross-process surface, framing has its own
# threat surface (untrusted peer over UDS / pipe).
src/daemon/**                @nexus-eng/runtime @nexus-eng/security
src/bin/nexus_agentd.rs      @nexus-eng/runtime @nexus-eng/security

# Validation harness: the source of truth for the benchmark report;
# changes here can quietly inflate or deflate the numbers.
scripts/**                   @nexus-eng/eval
benches/**                   @nexus-eng/eval
VALIDATION_REPORT.md         @nexus-eng/eval
